# Episode 1 — Google Form Setup

## What I Built
A form where clients enter their own details.
No manual data entry needed from the owner.
Form submit = automation starts automatically.

## Form Config
```
Title: Invoice Request Form

Q1: Client Name — Short answer — Required ON
Q2: Client Email — Short answer — Required ON
Q3: Service Description — Paragraph — Required ON
Q4: Invoice Amount ($) — Short answer — Required ON
Q5: Payment Due Date — Date — Required ON
```

## Form → Sheets Connection
```
Responses tab → Sheets icon
→ Connect to existing spreadsheet
→ Invoice Request Form
→ Create
```

## Extra Columns Added Manually in Sheet
```
G1: Status
H1: Invoice Sent
I1: Follow Up Sent
```

## Why I Did It This Way
Form handles client input — owner touches nothing.
Extra columns track workflow progress.
n8n updates these columns as work gets done.
Status starts empty — n8n sets it to Unpaid.
Invoice Sent starts empty — n8n sets it to Yes after sending.
This is how a real invoice tracking system works.

