# Episode 5 — Node 04 — Parse AI Response

## Node Info
```
Node Type : Code Node
Node Name : 04 - Parse AI Response
Language  : JavaScript
Mode      : Run Once for All Items
Job       : Extracts AI output and combines
            everything into one clean package
```

## Full Code
```javascript
const items = $input.all();
const results = [];

for (const item of items) {

  const rawText = item.json.output[0].content[0].text;
  const parsed = JSON.parse(rawText);

  const node02 = $('02 - Extract Invoice Data');

  results.push({
    json: {
      client_name   : node02.item.json['Client Name'],
      client_email  : node02.item.json['Client Email'],
      service       : node02.item.json['Service Description'],
      amount        : node02.item.json['Invoice Amount ($)'],
      due_date      : node02.item.json['Payment Due Date'],
      status        : node02.item.json.status,
      invoice_sent  : node02.item.json.invoice_sent,
      follow_up_sent: node02.item.json.follow_up_sent,
      subject       : parsed.subject,
      body          : parsed.body
    }
  });
}

return results;
```

## Why I Built It This Way
AI returns plain text. I cannot use it directly.
I parse it and pull out subject and body.
I combine Node 02 data here so everything is in one place.
Every node after this references Node 04 for data.
This is the central data hub of the workflow.

## Critical Things
```
OpenAI response path in n8n:
output[0].content[0].text ✅
message.content ❌

Node 02 reference:
$('02 - Extract Invoice Data').item.json['Client Name'] ✅
```

