# Episode 7 — Node 06 — Mark Invoice Sent

## Node Info
```
Node Type : Google Sheets — Update Row
Node Name : 06 - Mark Invoice Sent
Job       : Updates Sheet — Invoice Sent = Yes
```

## Config
```
Spreadsheet       : Invoice Request Form (Responses)
Sheet             : Form Responses 1
Column to match on: Client Email
Client Email value: {{ $('04 - Parse AI Response').item.json.client_email }}

Fields to update:
Invoice Sent → Yes
```

## Why I Built It This Way
After Node 05 Gmail Send, $json loses all data.
Only Gmail metadata remains — id, threadId, labelIds.
I must reference Node 04 directly to get client_email.
This is a pattern that repeats everywhere in n8n.
After any send or update node — reference the last data node by name.

